MUSI 373: Advanced Accompanying and Musicianship Skills. 3 credits.
Advanced study and techniques for accompanying choirs, vocal soloists, and instrumentalists. Additional instruction in keyboard reduction of orchestral scores for concertos, continuo/figured bass reading, lead-sheet reading, transposition, improvisation, transcription, and "playing by ear." Offered by Dewberry School of Music. Limited to three attempts.
