MUSI 455: Music as a Healing Art. 3 credits.
Study of the relationship between musical vibrations and the natural rhythms of the body. Topics include history of music and healing, theory of sound, cymatics, toning, and performance practice as well as a survey of vibrational healing modalities and related therapies. Considers listening examples as they apply to healing with music. Students sing and play instruments in directed improvisatory performance. Offered by Dewberry School of Music. May be repeated within the degree for a maximum 6 credits.
Recommended Prerequisite: Basic proficiency with instrument or voice or permission of instructor.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

