MUSI 464: Instrumental Music Methods I. 3 credits.
Prepares students to successfully plan, organize, and administer marching band and jazz ensemble programs in secondary public school music curriculum. Students spend three hours per week in class, and one hour per week observing and teaching in laboratory ensemble. Students also participate in field observation of music classes in public schools. Notes: For music majors only. Offered by Dewberry School of Music. Limited to three attempts.
Recommended Prerequisite: MUSI 214, 216, 273, and acceptance into the Music Education concentration.
