MUSI 515: Music in Computer Technology. 3 credits.
Overview computer use in music. Topics include principles of musical instrument digital interface (MIDI); synthesis; acoustics and sound processing; and musical composition using the computer. Explores music resources of Internet, and surveys multimedia applications in music history, theory, ear training, improvisation, and notation. Offered by Dewberry School of Music. May not be repeated for credit.
